\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Installing TrueType fonts in Windows XP
\f1\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\f0\b \cf0 1.
\f1\b0  \'ca \cf2 From the 'Start' menu select 'Control Panel' and then select the 'Appearance and Themes' category.\cf0 \
\

\f0\b 2.
\f1\b0  \'ca \cf2 Select 'Fonts' from the 'See Also' panel at the left of this screen. \cf0 \
\

\f0\b 3.
\f1\b0  \'ca \cf2 On the 'File' menu, select 'Install New Font...'\cf0 \
\

\f0\b 4.
\f1\b0  \'ca \cf2 Click the drive and folder that contain the fonts you want to add.\cf0 \
\

\f0\b 5.
\f1\b0  \'ca \cf2 To select more than one font to add, press and hold down the CTRL key, click the fonts you want, then click on 'OK'.\cf0 \
\

\f0\b 6.
\f1\b0  \'ca \cf2 Remember to backup your new font on a separate disk!\cf0 \
\
